1
00:01:55,019 --> 00:01:56,219
Here

2
00:01:56,319 --> 00:01:57,359
Have a taste

3
00:01:57,700 --> 00:01:58,680
This is my son-in-law

4
00:01:58,859 --> 00:02:00,439
brought back from a business trip to Dandong

5
00:02:00,500 --> 00:02:01,159
Kiwi berries

6
00:02:01,379 --> 00:02:02,040
Are they sweet?

7
00:02:02,099 --> 00:02:03,060
Of course, very sweet

8
00:02:03,099 --> 00:02:03,819
I can't eat them

9
00:02:04,219 --> 00:02:04,560
Old Liang

10
00:02:04,560 --> 00:02:05,640
No, I have diabetes

11
00:02:06,180 --> 00:02:06,760
Rudy

12
00:02:06,799 --> 00:02:07,379
Type 2

13
00:02:07,519 --> 00:02:08,240
diabetes

14
00:02:08,479 --> 00:02:09,080
Xiao Cai

15
00:02:09,159 --> 00:02:10,199
I also... well

16
00:02:10,780 --> 00:02:11,500
Look at this

17
00:02:11,500 --> 00:02:12,319
Fine

18
00:02:12,639 --> 00:02:13,759
I'll show some support

19
00:02:13,759 --> 00:02:14,240
Right

20
00:02:14,240 --> 00:02:14,719
Let me

21
00:02:14,719 --> 00:02:15,539
pick a soft one

22
00:02:15,740 --> 00:02:16,280
Okay

23
00:02:17,780 --> 00:02:18,340
A specialty

24
00:02:19,919 --> 00:02:20,860
Really good

25
00:02:21,580 --> 00:02:22,280
Boss Li

26
00:02:22,740 --> 00:02:25,020
Your son-in-law is really nice

27
00:02:25,080 --> 00:02:28,659
Thinking of his father-in-law first with good food

28
00:02:29,780 --> 00:02:31,979
Honest and family-oriented

29
00:02:32,039 --> 00:02:34,060
Spends his earnings on his wife

30
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:36,520
If you want a good life

31
00:02:36,759 --> 00:02:38,259
the woman must run the house

32
00:02:38,780 --> 00:02:39,900
This son-in-law of mine

33
00:02:40,080 --> 00:02:41,580
was personally promoted by me

34
00:02:41,860 --> 00:02:43,000
His main strengths are

35
00:02:43,099 --> 00:02:44,180
proactive and hardworking

36
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:45,060
honest and obedient

37
00:02:45,919 --> 00:02:46,879
I think

38
00:02:46,879 --> 00:02:48,699
in a marriage, living together

39
00:02:48,780 --> 00:02:50,719
two people must respect each other

40
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:52,060
understand each other

41
00:02:52,159 --> 00:02:53,979
and give each other some space

42
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:55,500
Uncles and Aunties

43
00:02:55,500 --> 00:02:56,460
don't you agree?

44
00:02:58,259 --> 00:02:58,879
Speak up

45
00:02:59,139 --> 00:03:00,300
How do you explain this?

46
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:01,439
I

47
00:03:01,840 --> 00:03:03,319
I might have slipped

48
00:03:03,580 --> 00:03:04,280
An accidental operation

49
00:03:04,280 --> 00:03:05,340
Make it up

50
00:03:05,340 --> 00:03:06,319
You're making things up again

51
00:03:07,039 --> 00:03:08,500
How is it so coincidental?

52
00:03:08,580 --> 00:03:09,699
With this female friend of yours

53
00:03:09,759 --> 00:03:10,759
this Qianqian

54
00:03:10,979 --> 00:03:12,860
you deleted all the chat logs with her

55
00:03:13,300 --> 00:03:14,639
But the chat logs with President Ma

56
00:03:14,639 --> 00:03:15,620
why weren't those deleted?

57
00:03:15,639 --> 00:03:18,340
And "Follow President Ma's lead"

58
00:03:18,639 --> 00:03:20,199
President Ma is my direct supervisor

59
00:03:20,199 --> 00:03:21,960
Don't change the subject on me

60
00:03:22,139 --> 00:03:24,780
Tell me what's going on with this Qianqian

61
00:03:24,939 --> 00:03:26,060
There's nothing going on between us

62
00:03:26,060 --> 00:03:27,740
We are completely innocent

63
00:03:29,819 --> 00:03:31,580
Your college sweetheart, right?

64
00:03:32,659 --> 00:03:34,919
She always kept you as a backup, right?

65
00:03:35,960 --> 00:03:37,719
I'm aware of all these details.

66
00:03:38,199 --> 00:03:40,159
Didn't I voluntarily confess before we got married?

67
00:03:40,300 --> 00:03:41,360
What are you mumbling about?

68
00:03:41,979 --> 00:03:42,939
Listen here, Wu Yuntang.

69
00:03:43,080 --> 00:03:44,180
She's already married.

70
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:45,479
Her second kid is already running errands.

71
00:03:45,539 --> 00:03:47,060
Why are you still so obsessed with her?

72
00:03:48,379 --> 00:03:49,520
There's one more thing.

73
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:50,560
That you aren't aware of.

74
00:03:50,560 --> 00:03:52,319
She just recently got divorced.

75
00:03:53,060 --> 00:03:54,039
Because of you?

76
00:03:54,039 --> 00:03:54,419
No.

77
00:03:54,419 --> 00:03:55,560
It has nothing to do with me.

78
00:03:55,560 --> 00:03:57,080
It was her French husband.

79
00:03:58,000 --> 00:03:59,020
He had an affair.

80
00:03:59,259 --> 00:04:01,199
He found a mistress from Belgium.

81
00:04:02,120 --> 00:04:04,159
I heard she's even a fashion model.

82
00:04:04,159 --> 00:04:04,819
A model?

83
00:04:04,819 --> 00:04:05,280
That's right.

84
00:04:05,740 --> 00:04:06,219
Pfft.

85
00:04:06,879 --> 00:04:08,539
Who cares about her messy business?

86
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:10,340
Let me tell you, Wu Yuntang.

87
00:04:10,599 --> 00:04:11,900
You better behave yourself.

88
00:04:12,300 --> 00:04:14,580
Did you hear she got divorced...

89
00:04:14,620 --> 00:04:16,100
...and decide you want to be her backup again?

90
00:04:16,899 --> 00:04:17,759
Confess honestly.

91
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:19,300
Aren't I honest enough?

92
00:04:19,980 --> 00:04:20,899
In your Li family...

93
00:04:20,899 --> 00:04:22,579
I never hit back or talk back.

94
00:04:22,579 --> 00:04:24,480
I hand over my salary and do all the housework.

95
00:04:24,480 --> 00:04:25,839
Isn't that exactly what you should do?

96
00:04:25,839 --> 00:04:27,259
Why should I have to do that?

97
00:04:27,579 --> 00:04:29,420
When have you ever cared about my feelings?

98
00:04:29,660 --> 00:04:31,040
Have you ever respected me?

99
00:04:31,180 --> 00:04:32,459
Respect you for what?

100
00:04:32,459 --> 00:04:34,160
Respect you for flirting with other people?

101
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:35,959
If you're going to put it that way...

102
00:04:35,959 --> 00:04:37,399
Then let me tell you something.

103
00:04:37,399 --> 00:04:38,139
A few days ago...

104
00:04:38,300 --> 00:04:40,379
I actually met up with Qianqian.

105
00:04:40,480 --> 00:04:42,540
You— But nothing happened!

106
00:04:42,600 --> 00:04:44,620
But seeing how you're acting now...

107
00:04:44,620 --> 00:04:45,920
I'm actually starting to regret that.

108
00:04:46,139 --> 00:04:47,360
You're hurting me!

109
00:04:48,019 --> 00:04:49,240
Regret?

110
00:04:49,379 --> 00:04:50,019
You regret it?

111
00:04:50,019 --> 00:04:51,579
If you regret it, go find her then!

112
00:04:51,579 --> 00:04:52,540
Get out!

113
00:04:52,779 --> 00:04:54,259
You're telling me to get out?

114
00:04:54,259 --> 00:04:55,339
This is my home too.

115
00:04:55,339 --> 00:04:56,339
What do you mean "your home"?

116
00:04:56,339 --> 00:04:57,699
My dad bought this house!

117
00:04:58,079 --> 00:04:58,500
You...

118
00:04:58,500 --> 00:04:59,120
You... I...

119
00:04:59,120 --> 00:05:00,279
What are you doing?

120
00:05:00,319 --> 00:05:01,439
Are you going to hit me?

121
00:05:01,439 --> 00:05:01,800
I...

122
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:03,139
I want a divorce.

123
00:05:04,579 --> 00:05:05,279
What did you say?

124
00:05:05,620 --> 00:05:06,399
Say that again.

125
00:05:07,079 --> 00:05:07,500
I...

126
00:05:09,439 --> 00:05:09,980
Want a divorce.

127
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:13,139
You're bringing up divorce with me?

128
00:05:13,420 --> 00:05:14,839
You are ridiculous.

129
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:21,120
This Little Wu...

130
00:05:22,399 --> 00:05:23,920
He is a wolf of Zhongshan,

131
00:05:24,339 --> 00:05:25,699
Ruthless once he gets his way.

132
00:05:27,019 --> 00:05:29,660
I'm usually very good at judging character.

133
00:05:29,980 --> 00:05:31,779
How did I miss the mark this time?

134
00:05:32,240 --> 00:05:33,500
You, good at judging character?

135
00:05:34,300 --> 00:05:36,420
You were the one who introduced Little Wu, right?

136
00:05:36,839 --> 00:05:38,639
I saw that at work, he was...

137
00:05:39,079 --> 00:05:40,319
Proactive and hardworking,

138
00:05:40,620 --> 00:05:41,620
Honest and simple,

139
00:05:42,300 --> 00:05:43,459
Dutiful,

140
00:05:43,540 --> 00:05:44,639
And bore burdens without complaint.

141
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:45,600
It was an act.

142
00:05:45,839 --> 00:05:47,139
He just wanted to suck up to you.

143
00:05:48,420 --> 00:05:50,319
Looking at the situation now,

144
00:05:50,360 --> 00:05:51,899
When Little Wu pursued Jiajia back then,

145
00:05:51,959 --> 00:05:53,259
His motives were impure.

146
00:05:54,220 --> 00:05:55,519
It was your nepotism.

147
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:56,879
You gave him an exceptional promotion.

148
00:05:57,220 --> 00:05:58,100
Of course.

149
00:05:58,459 --> 00:05:59,259
Actually, no.

150
00:06:00,019 --> 00:06:02,519
It was my subordinates doing it out of respect for me.

151
00:06:02,819 --> 00:06:04,180
It's all your fault.

152
00:06:04,459 --> 00:06:07,040
Think about how many people pursued me back then.

153
00:06:07,399 --> 00:06:08,019
Zhang Xiao.

154
00:06:08,220 --> 00:06:09,000
Cao Yang.

155
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:09,600
Yi Zan.

156
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:10,300
Ying Di.

157
00:06:10,339 --> 00:06:11,839
Who wasn't better than him?

158
00:06:11,839 --> 00:06:12,500
Honestly.

159
00:06:12,560 --> 00:06:13,339
Yeah.

160
00:06:13,699 --> 00:06:14,720
Didn't every single one of them...

161
00:06:14,720 --> 00:06:16,399
Get driven away by you?

162
00:06:17,579 --> 00:06:19,759
I just saw that Little Wu was wimpy,

163
00:06:20,019 --> 00:06:21,439
Honest and simple,

164
00:06:22,720 --> 00:06:24,459
And could stand your temper.

165
00:06:24,579 --> 00:06:25,420
It was an act.

166
00:06:25,420 --> 00:06:26,459
He was faking it all.

167
00:06:27,079 --> 00:06:27,519
No way.

168
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:28,920
I won't let him get away with this.

169
00:06:29,019 --> 00:06:29,600
Honey,

170
00:06:30,319 --> 00:06:31,779
Let's calm down first, okay?

171
00:06:32,879 --> 00:06:33,519
Yes.

172
00:06:34,779 --> 00:06:37,199
I think Little Wu just spoke out of anger.

173
00:06:37,980 --> 00:06:38,560
How about this.

174
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:40,500
I'll call him over personally.

175
00:06:40,639 --> 00:06:41,860
I'll talk to him face to face.

176
00:06:42,420 --> 00:06:43,399
It's no use what anyone says.

177
00:06:44,180 --> 00:06:45,819
I am definitely getting this divorce.

178
00:06:47,420 --> 00:06:48,079
No.

179
00:06:49,279 --> 00:06:50,300
I am very calm.

180
00:06:50,579 --> 00:06:52,279
It is absolutely not an impulse.

181
00:06:53,360 --> 00:06:54,259
Let me tell you,

182
00:06:54,500 --> 00:06:56,500
If Jiajia wasn't so...

183
00:06:57,180 --> 00:06:58,100
Obedient to me,

184
00:06:58,300 --> 00:07:00,060
Making it hard for me to speak up.

185
00:07:02,860 --> 00:07:03,620
Qianqian,

186
00:07:04,879 --> 00:07:06,339
It was your divorce

187
00:07:06,660 --> 00:07:07,720
That gave me courage.

188
00:07:08,339 --> 00:07:10,459
I've decided to go crazy for love once.

189
00:07:12,579 --> 00:07:13,399
Qianqian,

190
00:07:14,240 --> 00:07:16,699
I have so much to tell you.

191
00:07:17,579 --> 00:07:19,899
When do you have time for us to meet?

192
00:07:21,620 --> 00:07:22,519
You do your thing.

193
00:07:22,519 --> 00:07:23,959
I'm available whenever you call.

194
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:28,300
Little Zhang.

195
00:07:28,860 --> 00:07:30,319
What's my schedule for today?

196
00:07:30,980 --> 00:07:31,980
Let me take a look.

197
00:07:37,399 --> 00:07:38,740
This morning,

198
00:07:38,759 --> 00:07:41,339
Lunch with President Zhang of 2B1.

199
00:07:41,500 --> 00:07:43,199
And the subsequent itinerary,

200
00:07:43,199 --> 00:07:44,579
Is with this President Zhang,

201
00:07:44,579 --> 00:07:45,180
The two of you,

202
00:07:45,180 --> 00:07:47,379
Will go for a site visit together.

203
00:07:47,560 --> 00:07:48,740
After this visit,

204
00:07:48,740 --> 00:07:50,180
Let me see...

205
00:07:51,680 --> 00:07:52,480
Hello? Who is this?

206
00:07:53,180 --> 00:07:54,040
Dad.

207
00:07:55,420 --> 00:07:56,079
Boss Li.

208
00:07:58,779 --> 00:07:59,920
Old Li.

209
00:08:00,439 --> 00:08:01,220
What is it?

210
00:08:03,139 --> 00:08:03,980
About this matter...

211
00:08:05,560 --> 00:08:07,920
I've really been a bit busy lately.

212
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:08,779
How about this,

213
00:08:09,180 --> 00:08:11,000
I'll have my secretary schedule a time.

214
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:12,160
I'll make an appointment with you another day.

215
00:08:12,160 --> 00:08:12,620
Okay.

216
00:08:12,680 --> 00:08:14,019
Okay, bye-bye.

217
00:08:20,180 --> 00:08:20,759
See?

218
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:22,199
Overestimated yourself, didn't you?

219
00:08:22,699 --> 00:08:24,420
Here, call Uncle Ma directly.

220
00:08:24,639 --> 00:08:25,759
And have him fired.

221
00:08:26,019 --> 00:08:27,639
I bet that'll fix him.

222
00:08:28,220 --> 00:08:28,740
Child,

223
00:08:29,339 --> 00:08:30,420
if you do that,

224
00:08:30,740 --> 00:08:32,759
your divorce will be set in stone.

225
00:08:32,980 --> 00:08:34,860
There's no room for reconciliation.

226
00:08:35,220 --> 00:08:36,440
So be it.

227
00:08:36,779 --> 00:08:38,220
I don't want to be with him anyway.

228
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:41,159
Your Uncle Fan makes sense.

229
00:08:42,320 --> 00:08:43,480
Don't be impulsive.

230
00:08:47,279 --> 00:08:48,820
Let's hear what the folks think.

231
00:08:49,860 --> 00:08:51,500
How dare you, Wu Yuntang.

232
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:54,019
You don't know how good you have it.

233
00:08:54,159 --> 00:08:56,340
Marrying such a good wife like Jiajia.

234
00:08:56,340 --> 00:08:57,720
And you're still not satisfied.

235
00:08:57,879 --> 00:08:58,580
Let me tell you,

236
00:08:58,600 --> 00:09:00,779
you deserve to be stuck with my awful daughter-in-law.

237
00:09:01,480 --> 00:09:02,220
I'm telling you,

238
00:09:02,220 --> 00:09:04,159
that daughter-in-law of mine...

239
00:09:04,720 --> 00:09:06,919
I say, Auntie Cai,

240
00:09:08,460 --> 00:09:09,519
you mean,

241
00:09:09,779 --> 00:09:11,679
you agree Jiajia should divorce?

242
00:09:12,679 --> 00:09:13,639
Well, I...

243
00:09:13,639 --> 00:09:15,340
I didn't say that.

244
00:09:15,340 --> 00:09:15,820
Didn't you...

245
00:09:15,820 --> 00:09:17,559
Doesn't the old saying go,

246
00:09:18,179 --> 00:09:19,919
Better to destroy ten temples

247
00:09:20,039 --> 00:09:21,519
than one marriage.

248
00:09:21,820 --> 00:09:23,779
If you can make do, make do.

249
00:09:23,779 --> 00:09:24,919
But if worst comes to worst...

250
00:09:24,919 --> 00:09:26,080
You said nothing at all.

251
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:27,779
Old Li,

252
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:29,299
I understand you.

253
00:09:29,700 --> 00:09:31,200
We both have daughters.

254
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:31,919
Yes, right?

255
00:09:32,360 --> 00:09:33,980
And I'm a bit better off than you.

256
00:09:34,519 --> 00:09:35,580
I've been divorced.

257
00:09:36,620 --> 00:09:38,179
You call being divorced "better off"?

258
00:09:38,179 --> 00:09:40,039
No, I have experience.

259
00:09:40,220 --> 00:09:41,659
Experience makes an expert.

260
00:09:42,519 --> 00:09:43,620
Divorce,

261
00:09:43,679 --> 00:09:44,960
is really no fun.

262
00:09:45,279 --> 00:09:47,720
Don't do it if you can avoid it.

263
00:09:48,480 --> 00:09:49,240
Of course,

264
00:09:49,360 --> 00:09:51,259
if you absolutely must divorce,

265
00:09:52,440 --> 00:09:53,139
then you must.

266
00:09:54,059 --> 00:09:55,419
That's also like saying nothing.

267
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:56,100
No,

268
00:09:56,100 --> 00:09:57,700
I've always believed,

269
00:09:58,320 --> 00:10:00,120
that an unhappy marriage

270
00:10:00,120 --> 00:10:01,779
is not worth maintaining.

271
00:10:02,059 --> 00:10:04,679
Since Little Wu has had a change of heart,

272
00:10:04,679 --> 00:10:06,320
you can't force love.

273
00:10:06,320 --> 00:10:07,960
Listen to what Teacher Liu said.

274
00:10:08,179 --> 00:10:08,919
Of course,

275
00:10:09,559 --> 00:10:12,519
if Little Wu changes his mind back,

276
00:10:12,620 --> 00:10:13,779
You also said nothing.

277
00:10:14,120 --> 00:10:14,919
My suggestion,

278
00:10:16,159 --> 00:10:17,519
if there is no love left,

279
00:10:17,919 --> 00:10:19,740
then why not let go?

280
00:10:19,779 --> 00:10:21,399
This is very normal.

281
00:10:21,580 --> 00:10:23,480
Every man and woman

282
00:10:23,480 --> 00:10:26,100
has the right to love or not to love.

283
00:10:26,100 --> 00:10:28,480
Just say whether to divorce or not.

284
00:10:28,539 --> 00:10:29,559
My suggestion is,

285
00:10:29,620 --> 00:10:30,639
you can divorce,

286
00:10:31,019 --> 00:10:32,019
or you can not divorce.

287
00:10:32,200 --> 00:10:32,860
Divorce.

288
00:10:33,759 --> 00:10:34,500
You must divorce.

289
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:37,000
You must make a clean break with that Wu Yuntang.

290
00:10:37,620 --> 00:10:38,100
Dad,

291
00:10:38,320 --> 00:10:39,700
I have just one request now.

292
00:10:39,919 --> 00:10:41,340
Call that President Ma.

293
00:10:41,639 --> 00:10:43,399
Have him strip that ungrateful Wu Yuntang

294
00:10:43,399 --> 00:10:44,299
of all his titles.

295
00:10:45,779 --> 00:10:46,539
This...

296
00:10:46,919 --> 00:10:47,940
Here, use my phone.

297
00:10:47,940 --> 00:10:48,500
You call.

298
00:10:48,639 --> 00:10:49,559
Call right now.

299
00:10:50,519 --> 00:10:51,519
Tell him right now.

300
00:10:56,320 --> 00:10:56,919
Jiajia

301
00:10:58,679 --> 00:11:00,000
President Ma and I...

302
00:11:01,100 --> 00:11:02,320
used to have

303
00:11:02,320 --> 00:11:04,639
many disagreements on decisions.

304
00:11:06,240 --> 00:11:07,860
Now that I'm no longer in office,

305
00:11:09,100 --> 00:11:10,340
making this phone call

306
00:11:10,340 --> 00:11:11,600
might not work.

307
00:11:12,299 --> 00:11:13,059
It...

308
00:11:13,059 --> 00:11:15,019
It's really hard to say.

309
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:19,639
It might even

310
00:11:20,539 --> 00:11:21,940
be counterproductive

311
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:23,019
and humiliating.

312
00:11:23,240 --> 00:11:23,799
Don't you think?

313
00:11:24,039 --> 00:11:25,340
So what should we do?

314
00:11:25,559 --> 00:11:27,179
Just watch that ungrateful wolf Wu Yuntang

315
00:11:27,179 --> 00:11:28,419
and not be able to do anything?

316
00:11:28,960 --> 00:11:30,220
Sit down first.

317
00:11:30,440 --> 00:11:31,279
Listen to Dad.

318
00:11:31,759 --> 00:11:32,620
Listen to me.

319
00:11:34,220 --> 00:11:35,559
Here's what I think.

320
00:11:35,720 --> 00:11:37,179
Let's take this opportunity

321
00:11:37,720 --> 00:11:39,960
to reflect on ourselves first.

322
00:11:40,919 --> 00:11:41,580
Little Wu

323
00:11:42,059 --> 00:11:43,700
was introduced to you by me.

324
00:11:44,440 --> 00:11:45,779
I'll start with a self-criticism.

325
00:11:47,039 --> 00:11:47,940
Furthermore,

326
00:11:48,240 --> 00:11:48,860
well,

327
00:11:48,860 --> 00:11:49,559
shouldn't you

328
00:11:49,559 --> 00:11:51,759
also examine yourself?

329
00:11:52,440 --> 00:11:53,379
Don't you think

330
00:11:53,759 --> 00:11:55,419
that in many ways,

331
00:11:56,600 --> 00:11:58,139
you could have done better?

332
00:12:00,340 --> 00:12:01,759
For the situation today,

333
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:04,340
don't you bear some responsibility too?

334
00:12:20,460 --> 00:12:20,940
No way.

335
00:12:20,940 --> 00:12:22,299
Let me drink it. I'll drink it.

336
00:12:22,299 --> 00:12:23,299
I'm drinking it. No.

337
00:12:24,100 --> 00:12:26,120
Sister Li Jia, do you want a cappuccino or a latte?

338
00:12:26,399 --> 00:12:27,340
I'm not drinking.

339
00:12:29,480 --> 00:12:30,159
Then I'll drink it.

340
00:12:30,179 --> 00:12:31,039
I'll drink that latte.

341
00:12:31,039 --> 00:12:32,000
I still want to drink that latte.

342
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:33,960
I want to drink it. We agreed yesterday.

343
00:12:34,399 --> 00:12:36,460
Can you two care about me for a second?

344
00:12:36,759 --> 00:12:38,919
We care.

345
00:12:39,240 --> 00:12:40,399
If we didn't care about your business,

346
00:12:40,399 --> 00:12:41,519
why would we come here?

347
00:12:41,940 --> 00:12:42,580
Sister Jia.

348
00:12:42,980 --> 00:12:45,480
When I first met your husband, I said...

349
00:12:45,519 --> 00:12:47,120
You can't marry an engineering guy.

350
00:12:47,120 --> 00:12:47,840
Did I say that or not?

351
00:12:47,940 --> 00:12:49,279
I said that too.

352
00:12:49,340 --> 00:12:51,779
Give me a break. When did you two say that?

353
00:12:51,860 --> 00:12:52,919
I just remember you saying...

354
00:12:52,980 --> 00:12:54,460
Brother Wu is a really nice guy.

355
00:12:54,460 --> 00:12:55,820
Honest and reliable.

356
00:12:55,860 --> 00:12:57,159
He looks like a hidden gem.

357
00:12:57,159 --> 00:12:58,460
"Hidden gem," she said that.

358
00:12:59,039 --> 00:13:00,960
I want to marry someone like that in the future.

359
00:13:01,840 --> 00:13:04,759
Didn't we say that just to make you happy?

360
00:13:04,840 --> 00:13:05,539
Besides...

361
00:13:05,539 --> 00:13:07,759
How could you believe what us kids say?

362
00:13:08,259 --> 00:13:10,139
I actually believed what you kids said.

363
00:13:10,639 --> 00:13:12,139
Sister Jia, you're Type A blood, right?

364
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:13,240
That means you're gullible.

365
00:13:13,419 --> 00:13:14,679
And a Virgo.

366
00:13:14,759 --> 00:13:16,899
A typical lovesick mind.

367
00:13:17,340 --> 00:13:19,299
And my dad insisted on telling me...

368
00:13:19,360 --> 00:13:21,139
How great Little Wu is...

369
00:13:21,139 --> 00:13:22,220
Boundless future.

370
00:13:22,220 --> 00:13:24,419
Arranged marriages cause so much harm.

371
00:13:25,080 --> 00:13:27,759
And Wu Yuntang was chasing me relentlessly.

372
00:13:27,759 --> 00:13:28,879
A moment of confusion.

373
00:13:28,879 --> 00:13:30,220
Blinded.

374
00:13:31,639 --> 00:13:33,480
Are you two making fun of me?

375
00:13:33,480 --> 00:13:34,820
Or helping me come up with ideas?

376
00:13:34,840 --> 00:13:36,259
And you call yourselves volunteers.

377
00:13:36,879 --> 00:13:37,980
Helping you.

378
00:13:37,980 --> 00:13:39,980
We're definitely on your side, sister.

379
00:13:39,980 --> 00:13:40,340
Right.

380
00:13:40,340 --> 00:13:41,179
Just tell us.

381
00:13:41,539 --> 00:13:42,039
How to help.

382
00:13:44,259 --> 00:13:44,759
How about this.

383
00:13:44,759 --> 00:13:45,879
I have an idea.

384
00:13:46,179 --> 00:13:47,500
I'll go find him tomorrow.

385
00:13:47,500 --> 00:13:48,639
I'll give him a good scolding.

386
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:50,960
It's not appropriate for us to scold him, is it?

387
00:13:51,220 --> 00:13:51,899
Besides...

388
00:13:51,899 --> 00:13:54,039
What's the use of just scolding him?

389
00:13:54,360 --> 00:13:55,159
That makes sense.

390
00:13:55,159 --> 00:13:56,580
We still need to criticize and educate him.

391
00:13:56,580 --> 00:13:57,960
Make him pull back from the brink.

392
00:13:58,100 --> 00:13:59,159
Turn back to the shore.

393
00:14:00,679 --> 00:14:02,159
I'll call Wu Yuntang right now.

394
00:14:03,039 --> 00:14:03,460
You...

395
00:14:11,899 --> 00:14:12,340
Hello.

396
00:14:13,440 --> 00:14:14,240
Yes, I'm President Wu.

397
00:14:14,320 --> 00:14:14,899
Who is this?

398
00:14:16,159 --> 00:14:17,940
Xie Yingzi.

399
00:14:19,460 --> 00:14:21,519
It's the beautiful Yingzi.

400
00:14:22,399 --> 00:14:24,080
Why did you think of calling me?

401
00:14:25,759 --> 00:14:27,500
Li Jia made you call, right?

402
00:14:32,860 --> 00:14:33,740
That's fine.

403
00:14:34,320 --> 00:14:36,000
Then send me a location, okay?

404
00:14:47,340 --> 00:14:49,559
What kind of romantic luck have I stumbled into?

405
00:14:49,759 --> 00:14:51,039
The beautiful Yingzi.

406
00:14:51,039 --> 00:14:52,980
What made you think of summoning me alone?

407
00:14:53,039 --> 00:14:53,440
Sit.

408
00:14:53,720 --> 00:14:54,259
As you command.

409
00:14:54,740 --> 00:14:56,100
The reason I invited you here today...

410
00:14:56,100 --> 00:14:57,519
...is mainly to talk to you.

411
00:14:57,700 --> 00:14:59,440
What is going on with you and Sister Li Jia?

412
00:14:59,960 --> 00:15:00,500
You see?

413
00:15:00,840 --> 00:15:02,659
It was Li Jia who sent you to meet me, right?

414
00:15:03,879 --> 00:15:04,720
Where is she hiding?

415
00:15:04,879 --> 00:15:05,860
Is she eavesdropping somewhere?

416
00:15:05,860 --> 00:15:06,519
No.

417
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:08,600
No one sent me.

418
00:15:08,960 --> 00:15:10,820
I wanted to ask you myself.

419
00:15:11,700 --> 00:15:13,159
It's no big deal.

420
00:15:13,299 --> 00:15:15,259
Why must you get a divorce?

421
00:15:15,700 --> 00:15:16,440
You ask why?

422
00:15:16,700 --> 00:15:17,899
You have no idea.

423
00:15:18,139 --> 00:15:19,799
Being with her...

424
00:15:19,860 --> 00:15:23,080
I swallow insults and act submissive all day.

425
00:15:23,080 --> 00:15:25,440
Driving, running errands, cooking, washing dishes.

426
00:15:25,440 --> 00:15:27,919
I might even have to kneel on the washboard.

427
00:15:28,320 --> 00:15:28,980
Really.

428
00:15:30,519 --> 00:15:31,360
So what?

429
00:15:31,980 --> 00:15:33,039
Isn't it said that once married...

430
00:15:33,039 --> 00:15:34,679
...every husband is like this?

431
00:15:34,980 --> 00:15:36,139
But I've had enough!

432
00:15:36,519 --> 00:15:37,460
I, Wu Yuntang...

433
00:15:37,460 --> 00:15:39,440
...even if I were an AI robot...

434
00:15:39,440 --> 00:15:42,139
...would have reached the moment of developing self-awareness...

435
00:15:42,179 --> 00:15:43,360
...and awakening by now.

436
00:15:43,360 --> 00:15:44,080
Nonsense!

437
00:15:44,500 --> 00:15:45,460
You're talking nonsense!

438
00:15:46,639 --> 00:15:47,360
Who are you?

439
00:15:48,419 --> 00:15:49,360
Keke, right?

440
00:15:49,840 --> 00:15:51,820
You were eavesdropping inside just now, weren't you?

441
00:15:52,100 --> 00:15:53,759
What "had enough," what "awakening"?

442
00:15:53,759 --> 00:15:54,879
Let me tell you.

443
00:15:54,960 --> 00:15:57,080
That's called being fickle and having an affair.

444
00:15:57,080 --> 00:15:58,100
Do you admit it or not?

445
00:15:58,200 --> 00:16:00,299
Do you think we don't know about Qianqian?

446
00:16:01,320 --> 00:16:02,360
Oh, you're talking about that.

447
00:16:03,879 --> 00:16:06,120
I am indeed considering that aspect.

448
00:16:06,200 --> 00:16:07,179
I admit it.

449
00:16:07,240 --> 00:16:08,820
What can you do to me?

450
00:16:08,820 --> 00:16:09,240
I...

451
00:16:10,460 --> 00:16:12,779
I really can't do anything to him.

452
00:16:13,399 --> 00:16:14,059
Brother Wu.

453
00:16:14,480 --> 00:16:16,379
You have to have some conscience.

454
00:16:16,500 --> 00:16:17,259
Think about it.

455
00:16:17,539 --> 00:16:19,580
If you hadn't latched onto Li Jia back then...

456
00:16:19,580 --> 00:16:20,840
...would you be where you are today?

457
00:16:21,799 --> 00:16:22,600
President Wu?

458
00:16:24,179 --> 00:16:25,820
That's not necessarily true.

459
00:16:26,220 --> 00:16:27,200
I, Wu Yuntang...

460
00:16:27,899 --> 00:16:29,080
Peking University, Tsinghua...

461
00:16:29,080 --> 00:16:30,019
...I've attended them all.

462
00:16:30,039 --> 00:16:31,159
Or rather, I haven't.

463
00:16:31,159 --> 00:16:32,679
Why mention them if you haven't?

464
00:16:32,720 --> 00:16:34,460
But I believe...

465
00:16:34,500 --> 00:16:36,700
...gold will eventually be spent.

466
00:16:36,700 --> 00:16:37,139
Huh?

467
00:16:37,240 --> 00:16:39,220
No, eventually panic.

468
00:16:39,279 --> 00:16:40,299
Shine.

469
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:42,879
Shouldn't you thank Grandpa Li for that?

470
00:16:42,879 --> 00:16:44,519
For letting you shine?

471
00:16:44,899 --> 00:16:47,759
You don't know Li Jia's temper.

472
00:16:48,320 --> 00:16:51,440
Compared to our Qianqian's gentleness and care...

473
00:16:51,440 --> 00:16:53,080
...and understanding nature...

474
00:16:53,080 --> 00:16:54,700
...she is miles behind.

475
00:16:54,820 --> 00:16:55,440
Nonsense!

476
00:16:55,919 --> 00:16:56,679
Shut up!

477
00:16:56,740 --> 00:16:57,860
We are criticizing you here!

478
00:16:57,899 --> 00:16:59,379
You're not allowed to badmouth our Sister Li Jia!

479
00:16:59,679 --> 00:17:00,320
What's wrong?

480
00:17:01,080 --> 00:17:02,700
Can't I talk about her many flaws?

481
00:17:02,799 --> 00:17:03,799
I insist on saying it.

482
00:17:03,799 --> 00:17:04,700
To tell the truth...

483
00:17:05,220 --> 00:17:06,299
...Li Jia...

484
00:17:06,299 --> 00:17:09,059
...is just a tigress sleeping beside me.

485
00:17:09,579 --> 00:17:10,000
No.

486
00:17:10,519 --> 00:17:12,000
Fiercer than a tigress.

487
00:17:12,119 --> 00:17:14,720
She's simply a devil, a demoness!

488
00:17:15,079 --> 00:17:16,500
Wu Yuntang, you big jerk!

489
00:17:19,039 --> 00:17:19,539
You

490
00:17:19,880 --> 00:17:20,619
Fine

491
00:17:20,920 --> 00:17:22,579
You were eavesdropping inside the whole time, right?

492
00:17:23,259 --> 00:17:24,720
All right, all right, you two

493
00:17:25,440 --> 00:17:26,619
I cannot win an argument with you

494
00:17:26,880 --> 00:17:27,500
I am leaving

495
00:17:28,500 --> 00:17:29,720
See you at the Marriage Registration Office

496
00:17:29,740 --> 00:17:30,700
Fine, see you there

497
00:17:30,720 --> 00:17:31,819
Whoever does not go is a little dog

498
00:17:31,819 --> 00:17:32,599
Sister, sister

499
00:17:34,559 --> 00:17:36,339
Jiajia, what are you doing?

500
00:17:36,339 --> 00:17:37,400
Exactly, sis

501
00:17:37,400 --> 00:17:39,220
There is really no room to turn back like this

502
00:17:39,220 --> 00:17:40,240
Then so be it

503
00:17:40,259 --> 00:17:41,480
I am definitely divorcing

504
00:17:43,099 --> 00:17:44,220
Calm down

505
00:17:44,220 --> 00:17:45,220
That is enough

506
00:18:49,339 --> 00:18:50,119
Qianqian

507
00:18:51,619 --> 00:18:53,039
What are you doing here?

508
00:18:56,279 --> 00:18:57,519
Look at this

509
00:19:00,339 --> 00:19:01,299
Back to being free

510
00:19:02,240 --> 00:19:03,339
Congrats

511
00:19:03,519 --> 00:19:05,460
I came straight from the Marriage Registration Office

512
00:19:05,880 --> 00:19:07,259
You sure are decisive

513
00:19:07,799 --> 00:19:08,619
How is it so fast?

514
00:19:10,119 --> 00:19:11,420
It is not because of me, is it?

515
00:19:11,500 --> 00:19:12,559
Of course it is because of you

516
00:19:13,279 --> 00:19:13,940
Of course

517
00:19:14,339 --> 00:19:16,539
My marriage with Li Jia

518
00:19:16,660 --> 00:19:17,420
at its core

519
00:19:17,460 --> 00:19:19,559
also had irreconcilable problems

520
00:19:19,880 --> 00:19:20,819
That explains it

521
00:19:23,480 --> 00:19:24,700
As long as it is not my fault, good

522
00:19:25,240 --> 00:19:26,720
I really do not want to be a homewrecker

523
00:19:27,140 --> 00:19:29,240
You know my happy marriage with my ex husband

524
00:19:29,500 --> 00:19:31,299
was ruined by that Belgian mistress

525
00:19:31,559 --> 00:19:32,559
I hate mistresses so much

526
00:19:32,559 --> 00:19:33,640
I absolutely despise mistresses

527
00:19:33,640 --> 00:19:34,259
Right

528
00:19:34,279 --> 00:19:35,599
Mistresses are awful

529
00:19:35,599 --> 00:19:36,259
Mistresses are really darn it

530
00:19:36,259 --> 00:19:36,819
Darn it

531
00:19:36,920 --> 00:19:37,599
Seriously

532
00:19:40,880 --> 00:19:41,759
But Qianqian

533
00:19:42,680 --> 00:19:43,940
I just think

534
00:19:44,400 --> 00:19:46,279
you should let go of your worries

535
00:19:46,740 --> 00:19:47,259
Look

536
00:19:47,420 --> 00:19:49,420
In a flash we are already past thirty

537
00:19:50,200 --> 00:19:52,160
If we do not chase our own happiness now

538
00:19:52,579 --> 00:19:53,720
it will be too late

539
00:19:56,299 --> 00:19:58,240
What you are saying really makes sense

540
00:19:58,240 --> 00:19:58,839
Right?

541
00:19:59,240 --> 00:20:00,099
But

542
00:20:01,220 --> 00:20:02,980
if you marry me

543
00:20:03,640 --> 00:20:05,859
will our marriage definitely be happy?

544
00:20:17,180 --> 00:20:18,579
Since Little Wu's heart

545
00:20:18,579 --> 00:20:19,940
is no longer with you,

546
00:20:20,400 --> 00:20:22,099
I think it's better to let him go.

547
00:20:24,319 --> 00:20:25,579
On this matter,

548
00:20:26,640 --> 00:20:27,819
Dad is responsible.

549
00:20:28,400 --> 00:20:28,859
Dad,

550
00:20:29,099 --> 00:20:30,940
this has nothing to do with you.

551
00:20:31,660 --> 00:20:32,579
Growing up,

552
00:20:32,960 --> 00:20:34,660
schools had to be top-tier,

553
00:20:35,420 --> 00:20:36,819
choosing a college major,

554
00:20:37,559 --> 00:20:39,259
jobs had to be easy and respectable,

555
00:20:39,680 --> 00:20:40,420
and a partner...

556
00:20:41,380 --> 00:20:42,279
Isn't this just...

557
00:20:44,759 --> 00:20:45,380
my fault?

558
00:20:47,359 --> 00:20:47,859
Dad,

559
00:20:48,299 --> 00:20:49,640
actually, these past couple of days,

560
00:20:49,700 --> 00:20:50,759
I've been thinking too.

561
00:20:51,279 --> 00:20:53,380
Wu Yuntang and that female classmate of his,

562
00:20:54,059 --> 00:20:55,660
it was a bit less than love,

563
00:20:55,880 --> 00:20:57,220
but a bit more than friendship.

564
00:20:57,519 --> 00:20:59,400
If I hadn't kept such a close watch,

565
00:20:59,980 --> 00:21:01,220
and been a bit more oblivious,

566
00:21:01,660 --> 00:21:03,140
maybe it wouldn't have come to this.

567
00:21:03,140 --> 00:21:04,019
True.

568
00:21:04,599 --> 00:21:06,400
I'm exactly the same way.

569
00:21:06,700 --> 00:21:08,359
Wanting to win every battle,

570
00:21:08,539 --> 00:21:10,220
only to lose the entire war.

571
00:21:10,940 --> 00:21:12,559
Daughter, you take after me.

572
00:21:12,559 --> 00:21:13,480
Is that a good thing?

573
00:21:13,819 --> 00:21:14,539
Jiajia,

574
00:21:14,960 --> 00:21:16,140
here to see your dad again?

575
00:21:16,140 --> 00:21:16,880
Uncle.

576
00:21:18,140 --> 00:21:19,720
Why isn't that...

577
00:21:20,019 --> 00:21:21,099
Old Liang, you...

